Jekyll blog hosted on GitHub Pages at adamsoliev.github.io

Structure
---------
_config.yml             Site configuration
_layouts/
  default.html          Base HTML layout (includes MathJax)
  post.html             Blog post layout
_posts/                 Blog posts (YYYY-MM-DD-title.md)
assets/
  css/
    style.css           Main styles
    syntax.css          Code syntax highlighting (Rouge)
  images/               Post images
30-countdown/           Standalone countdown page
about.md                About page
index.html              Home page with post list
feed.xml                RSS feed

URLs
----
/                       Home (post list)
/blog/<title>/          Blog posts
/about                  About page
/30-countdown           Countdown timer
/feed.xml               RSS feed

Adding a post
-------------
1. Create _posts/YYYY-MM-DD-title.md
2. Add front matter:
   ---
   layout: post
   title: "Title"
   date: YYYY-MM-DD
   ---
3. Put images in assets/images/
4. Reference images: ![alt](/assets/images/file.png)
5. git add, commit, push

Local preview
-------------
jekyll serve
# http://localhost:4000
